(50, 'blog', '5 Steps to Get the Most Money Selling an Old or Broken iPad', 'blog/5-steps-to-get-the-most-money-selling-an-old-or-broken-ipad', 'Do you have an old or broken iPad just sitting around collecting dust? Why not recycle your old iPad and earn some extra cash by doing so? The longer you hold onto your iPad the more it will lose its value even if you have only used it a few times. ', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">5 Steps to Get the Most Money Selling an Old or Broken iPad</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Do you have an old or broken iPad just sitting around collecting dust? Why not recycle your old iPad and earn some extra cash by doing so? The longer you hold onto your iPad the more it will lose its value even if you have only used it a few times. </p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Steps to Sell Your Used iPad for the Most Cash</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Step 1: Back it up</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">If you don\'t have anything important you wish to save then you can skip this step. However if you have photos, contacts, or anything else that you want to transfer to your new iPad then this as an important step for you. </p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">The easiest way to backup your iPad (and not use up all your iCloud storage) is by plugging it into your computer and opening iTunes.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Once you plug in your iPad and open iTunes, it will automatically start backing it up. If for some reason it doesn\'t do so you can also manually start the back up process and save all your important information for future use. </p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Step 2: Sign out of iCloud</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Open up your settings, tap on your name, scroll down the page and click “Sign Out.” You’ll be prompted to enter your password and then hit “Turn Off.” If your iPad is broken and you cant sign out from the iPad you can also sign out of your iCloud account remotely from your computer.<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\"></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Step 3: Erase your iPad</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Go back to your settings. This time, go to <i>General > Reset > Erase All Content and Settings</i>. You may be prompted to enter a password. After select \"<i>Erase iPad</i>\".</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Step 4: Gather your iPads accessories and box that it came with</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">If you don\'t have the accessories or box anymore do not worry you can still sell it. But, if you do have them it will help bring up the value ensuring you get the most cash for your iPad.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">? Original iPad box</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">? Apple charging cable</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">? Apple wall adapter</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">? Headphone (if unused in original packaging)</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Step 5: Find the best place to sell your iPad for the best price</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">There are many ways and places that you can sell your iPad.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Option 1: Sell your iPad yourself</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">You can sell your iPad through sites like Craigslist, Offer Up, or Facebook Marketplace. However you will have to deal with buyers haggling you on price or people flaking on the meet up. After you find a buyer you still have to set up a time and place to meet that is OK for both parties. This can be frustrating and often times just not worth the hassle.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Option 2: Sell it to a 3rd party retailer</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">You can sell your iPad through eBay or Amazon but you will be charged an arm and a leg on fees. Your carrier store like Verizon or AT&T also buyback old iPad\'s but only offer store credit that you have to spend at their stores. Like the old phrase goes \"<i>Cash is KING</i>\"</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Option 3: Get a quote from us and sell your iPad today</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\">Here at <a href=\"https://www.ocbuyback.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">OCBuyBack.com</a> we have an easy to use process without any fees or tricks. After you enter your iPads model and condition you will receive an instant quote. We will provide you with a free prepaid shipping label and a shipping kit if you do not have a box. We also offer local drop at our location in Brea California.  Next select the payment method you prefer; check or PayPal. Payments are processed within 24 hours of your device being received and inspected.  We make selling your old iPad super simple without the hassle. Let us do the hard work for you!</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: \"Open Sans\", sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https://www.ocbuyback.com/sell/tablet/apple\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">Click here to get an instant quote for your used iPad and start selling today!</a></p>', '50-blog.jpg', 1, '2019-01-24 13:28:59', '2019-01-24 13:29:58'),
(52, 'blog', 'iPhone Keynote Speech 2018 - The Highlights', 'blog/iphone-keynote-speech-2018-the-highlights', '3 new phones and the Apple Watch 4 would be hitting the market in the coming months.', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Thousands of excited tech-fans flocked to Cupertino, California on Wednesday September 12th in order to get a sneak peek at the newest products which will soon be available. The event took place in the Steve Jobs Theater at Apple HQ and the announcements were widely met with enthusiasm. Fans were excited to hear that 3 new phones and the Apple Watch 4 would be hitting the market in the coming months. Just in time for Christmas of course!</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">iPhone Xs</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">The iPhone Xs uses the same super retina display that was so popular on the iPhone X. This OLED technology is able to capture colors and contrast with more accuracy than any previous display. The screen is slightly bigger than that of the iPhone X at 5.8 inches. The phone is also installed with state of the art processing technology. The A12 Bionic chip is capable of performing 5 trillion operations per second. Coincidentally, the A11 chip was only able to perform 600 billion operations per second. In addition, the image capturing quality of the Xs has been improved with smarter HDR technology. This will reduce the amount of blur on photos even when they are taken at high speeds. Apple has also announced that the battery life of an Xs will be around 30 minutes longer than its predecessor.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Features:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Six-core CPU</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Four-core GPU</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	IP68 waterproof rating</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Storage from 64GB to 512GB</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	7 MP front camera</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	12 MP dual Camera</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Available for shipping now</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">RRP: $999</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">iPhone Xs Max</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">The Xs Max boasts the largest screen out of any apple phone in history. At 6.5 inches this device will give users an incredibly satisfying viewing experience using the latest display technology. Much like the Xs, it has super retina display and the latest in OLED technology. Watching videos on the go has never been so immersive!</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Features:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Six-core CPU</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Four-core GPU</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	IP68 waterproof rating</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Storage from 64GB to 512GB</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	7 MP front camera</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	12 MP dual Camera</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Available for shipping now</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">RRP: $1099</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">iPhone XR</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">The introduction of the iPhone XR was welcoming news for iPhone lovers looking for an upgrade without breaking the bank. It has been compared to the iPhone 5c due to its smaller display and slightly downsized features. It comes in a variety of different colours and has been tipped as a product at the top of most children’s Christmas lists this Winter.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Features:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Six-core CPU</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Four-core GPU</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	IP68 waterproof rating</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	Storage from 16GB to 512GB</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	5 MP front camera</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">?	9 MP dual Camera</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Available for shipping from October</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">RRP: $749</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Apple Watch 4</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Announcement of the new Apple Watch will be mellifluous to many. One of the main complaints about the Apple Watch 3 was issues with cellular connection and the size of the display. Apple have confronted both these problems and guaranteed a new, flawless version.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Available for shipping now:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">RRP $499</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">After the Keynote conference many have already begun drafting their Christmas Lists!&nbsp;</p>', '52-blog.jpg', 1, '2019-01-24 13:44:13', NULL),
(53, 'blog', 'Samsung Galaxy 10 Release Date and What to Expect', 'blog/samsung-galaxy-10-release-date-and-what-to-expect', '', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Samsung Galaxy S10 &amp; S10 Plus Release Date and What to Expect</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">While the Samsung Galaxy S9 was one of this year\'s hottest Android smartphones, the Samsung Galaxy S10 is under the works. Here is what we should expect from Samsung\'s next best smartphone.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">There have been a few leaks and rumors about the Samsung lineup, including a lite version and an ultra 5G model. Keep reading to find out the details on the display, screen, camera, specifications and release date.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Display &amp; Design:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Samsung CEO DJ Koh reported the S10 lineup will come with radical changes one of those are the \"amazing array of color options. In addition to bright yellow and green options, Samsung may use ceramic fo the rear panel on a black and white Galaxy S10. The ceramic provides a high shine and is also very strong which could help resist scratches and marks more effectively.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">In December, the famous Samsung leaker Ice Universe offered us a glimpse of what he believes the upcoming Galaxy S10 will look like based on a photo of the screen protector. He believes the bezels will be nearly non-existent on the Galaxy S10. The phone will show nearly a 100 percent screen to body ratio, thanks to cutouts in the AMOLED display for the camera sensors.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">There may be three versions of the Galaxy S10, according to sources who spoke with Bloomberg. Rumor has is that the upcoming phones are referred to under the codename Beyond; Beyond 1 and Beyond 2 which are likely the Galaxy S10 and Galaxy S10 Plus. At Least two model swill reportedly feature the fingerprint -on-display (FOD) technology as well as AMOLED screens. Sources also refer to the Beyond 0, which is possibly a Galaxy S10 Lite a budget friendly version with a side mounted fingerprint sensor.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">The Wall Street Journal reports the display sizes for the Samsung Galaxy S10 would range from 5.8 inches to 6.4 inches, and that a future 5G model would feature a massive 6.7 inch screen.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Ming-Chi Kuo claims there will be one model with 5.8-inch display, one with a 6.1, and one with a 6.4 display, and that the two high end models will have an in-display fingerprint sensor.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Release Date:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">No one really knows the exact release date of Samsung\'s newest smartphone. However, The Bell says Samsung is aiming for a January 2019 release for the Galaxy S10 at the annual CES trade show in Las Vegas. Others rumor the release date to be Feb-Mar 2019 but remains unknown.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Camera:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Chinese social media platform Weibo, has shown an image of the Galaxy S10 screen protector confirming the cutout of the dual selfie cameras. According to 91Mobiles the Galaxy S10 has 3 rear cameras with one standard, one wide angle and one telephoto lens (sitting horizontally on the top third of the phone), 2 front cameras.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">All in all anticipate richer photos and better spatial perception on this new model. Samsung may increase camera performance by adding more lenses. Earlier this year Sammobile predicted the Galaxy S10 will come with three camera lenses on the back. The main lens will be the same 12-megapixel variable aperture lens joined by a 16-megapixel wide -angle lens with a 123-degree field of view. The third lense seems to be the as the S9 Plus- a 13-megapixel lens, likely equipped with a 2x telephoto zoom. The Wall Street Journal claims the Galaxy S10 will come with four rear camera lens and two front facing cameras.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Security:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Samsung may introduce a new fingerprint sensor. ET News reported that Samsung will use Qualcomm\'s third generation ultrasonic in display fingerprint sensors in its upcoming Galaxy S10 handsets. Qualcomm\'s technology can capture 3d Fingerprint data, allowing for higher accuracy and better security.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Software &amp; Special Features:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">According to Digital Trends there is a possibility that the Galaxy S10 will feature improved health apps. Let\'s Go Digital recently patented a new technology that allows a Samsung app to determine your skin type and can suggest recommendations to limit sun exposure. The app will apparently used photos of different parts of your body to determine skin type and constantly provide you with tips and measure your UV exposure.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Galaxy versions include: Galaxy S10 Lite, Galaxy S10, and Galaxy S10 5G.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">6.44-inch display infinity O display that has a cutout drilled into the screen panel to ensure a full-screen display without incorporating a notch. One of the versions of the S10 will support ultra high speed 5G networks. 5G is a new wireless standard that promises extremely fast data speeds and potentially less congestion than today\'s 4G LTE standard.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Specifications:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">According to digital Trends It is likely Samsung will use its Exynos 9820 chipset for the Galaxy S10 which Samsung claims is 20-percent better than its predecessor and 40-percent more efficient. The new Exynos 9820 chipset will have a dedicated Neural Processing Unit (NPU) to support artificial intelligence tasks, and 8K video at 30 frames per second.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Samsung Galaxy S10 &amp; S10 Plus Specifications:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Performance</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Octa Core (Dual Core+ Dual core + Quad Core)</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Samsung Exynos 9 Octa</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">6 GB RAM</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Display</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">6.44 inches (16.36cm)</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">1440x2960 px, 511 PPI</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Super Amoled</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Camera</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">16MP + 16MP + 13MP Triple Primary Cameras</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">LED Flash</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">8MP + 5MP Dual Front Cameras</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Battery</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">3700 MAH</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Fast Charging</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">USB Type-C Port</p>', '53-blog.jpg', 1, '2019-01-24 13:47:14', NULL),
(54, 'blog', 'Apple\'s Latest iOS 12 Features and Improvements', 'blog/apple-s-latest-ios-12-features-and-improvements', 'The newest version of iOS 12 is supposed to make your iPhone experience faster, more responsive and more delightful according to Apple.', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">In 2017, forecasters predict that around 223 million people in the U.S. will be using a smartphone which is about 83.8% of all mobile users. Out of these 223 million users over 90 million will own an iPhone making Apple’s iOS the leading operating system in America next to Android. The newest version of iOS 12 is supposed to make your iPhone experience faster, more responsive and more delightful according to Apple. Here are the top major changes happening with iOS 12, I’m sure it will help one of you 90 million plus iPhone users.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">First up, Performance, the iOS has been enhanced for a faster and more responsive experience all around. The regular things you do like launching camera or typing with the keyboard will happen faster than ever. This will also help when your doing a lot of things on your device all at once. These enhancements are said to improve performance on all supported devices, going all the way back to iPhone 5s. Apple claims you will notice up to 70% faster swipe to camera, up to 50% faster key board display and up to 2x faster app launch under heavy workload.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Later this Fall, the operating system will allow you to FaceTime with up to 32 people all at once. You can start group FaceTime right from a group thread in Messages or join an active one at any time. Making this a handy solution especially for those who are constantly on the go.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Next Memoji will now allow you to easily create a Memoji to match your personality and mood. This will allow you to make an many alter egos as you want to use in Messages and FaceTime. The upgraded iOS iPhone version will also allow you to choose from four new Animoji-koala, tiger, ghost, or T.rex- to inject fun into your next messages or FaceTime. Now you can be more expressive than ever on your mobile phone.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Lastly, you will be able to liven up the conversation with camera effects. Add personality to Messages and FaceTime right from the in-app camera. Create and share a photo or video with Animoji, Memoji, cool filters, animated text effects, fun stickers and more.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Other features included with iOS 12:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	An Apple Books app that replaces iBooks.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	A “For You” section in the Photos app.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	Notifications are grouped and now have a “manage” tab.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	The Do Not Disturb During Bedtime feature changes how notifications are handled at night.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	Safari now includes Intelligent Tracking Prevention. With this feature, you can disable social media “like” and “share” buttons.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	Maps app now includes first-party data.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	CarPlay now features the ability to run third-party navigation applications.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">•	Devices with Face ID, iOS 12 lets you add two faces for authentication now, instead of only one.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Now that you know what changes came about the newest iOS version go ahead and test it out. I know my family and I had tons of fun playing with the new Memoji and Animoji. Is this the worlds most advanced mobile operating system? I say so far, Yes! You can’t go wrong if 90 million users are using an iPhone.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">Sources:</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">https://www.statista.com/statistics/236550/percentage-of-us-population-that-own-a-iphone-smartphone/</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">https://www.apple.com/ios/ios-12/</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.58; font-size: 21px; letter-spacing: -0.063px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif;\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_mobile_operating_systems</p>', '54-blog.jpg', 1, '2019-01-24 14:08:06', NULL);
